    "reasoning": "To implement the TopModule according to the specification:\n\n1. Define the module interface with inputs and outputs as specified.\n2. For out_both: each bit should be 1 only if both the current bit and its neighbor to the left are 1. Since in[99] has no neighbor to the left, out_both[99] must be 0.\n3. For out_any: each bit should be 1 if either the current bit or its neighbor to the right is 1. Since in[0] has no neighbor to the right, out_any[0] must be 0.\n4. For out_different: each bit should be 1 if the current bit is different from its neighbor to the left, treating the vector as wrapping around so that in[0]'s neighbor to the left is in[99].\n\nThe implementation needs to carefully handle indexing for neighbors, especially for boundary cases. The Verilog convention for arrays is that in[99:0] maps to elements 0 through 99. So in[99] is the last element, and in[0] is the first element. This implies:\n- out_both[99] = 0 (no left neighbor)\n- out_any[0] = 0 (no right neighbor)\n- For out_different, we access in[99] for in[0]'s left neighbor\n\nAll outputs are purely combinational logic, thus using always @(*) blocks. To avoid syntax errors, ensure correct bit indexing and array references. No reset needed for combinational logic.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input  [99:0] in,\n    output [99:0] out_both,\n    output [99:0] out_any,\n    output [99:0] out_different\n);\n\n    // out_both: Each bit is 1 if both the current bit and its left neighbor are 1\n    // out_both[99] is 0 because there is no left neighbor\n    always @(*) begin\n        for (int i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin\n            if (i == 99) begin\n                out_both[i] = 1'b0;\n            end else begin\n                out_both[i] = in[i] & in[i + 1];\n            end\n        end\n    end\n\n    // out_any: Each bit is 1 if either the current bit or its right neighbor is 1\n    // out_any[0] is 0 because there is no right neighbor\n    always @(*) begin\n        for (int i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin\n            if (i == 0) begin\n                out_any[i] = 1'b0;\n            end else begin\n                out_any[i] = in[i] | in[i - 1];\n            end\n        end\n    end\n\n    // out_different: Each bit is 1 if the current bit is different from its left neighbor\n    // For wrapping, in[0]'s left neighbor is in[99]\n    always @(*) begin\n        for (int i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin\n            if (i == 0) begin\n                out_different[i] = in[i] ^ in[99];\n            end else begin\n                out_different[i] = in[i] ^ in[i - 1];\n            end\n        end\n    end\n\nendmodule"
}
